    <div class="container">

      <lead>KIT is a service that connects people at home with their loved ones traveling abroad using Periscope, the smart backpack system.</lead>

<dl>
  <dt>How does it work?</dt> 

<dd>The person wearing the Periscope backpack is equipped with high resolution, non-obtrusive cameras that create stop-motion footage while they are traveling, the cameras are attached at the users discretion, although most tend to put them on the straps of their backpacks, giving viewers at home a personal point of view of what it is like to travel with them. Haptic sensors in the backpack allow for users at home to connect with travelers in a physical aspect - no matter how far away they are. </dd>
</dl>
